---
import FlowLayout from "../layouts/FlowLayout.astro";
---

<FlowLayout
  title="About – Ahmad Madi"
  step={2}
  total={5}
  backHref="/"
  nextHref="/work"
>
  <section class="space-y-8">
    <header class="space-y-4">
      <p class="eyebrow">01 — About</p>
      <h1
        class="font-display text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight text-paper-100"
      >
        The short version.
      </h1>
      <p class="max-w-2xl text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed text-paper-300">
        I've spent about five years building and running cloud systems other
        people depend on. Internal tools, backend services, the kind of
        infrastructure that only gets noticed when it breaks. My job is to make
        sure it doesn't.
      </p>
      <p class="max-w-2xl leading-relaxed text-paper-500">
        I care about the boring parts done well. Clear APIs. Automation that
        does the obvious thing. Migrations that don't page anyone at 3am.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-paper-200">What I'm good at</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2.5 text-sm text-paper-400">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="mt-2 h-px w-3 shrink-0 bg-accent"></span>
            Backend APIs and services built to scale
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="mt-2 h-px w-3 shrink-0 bg-accent"></span>
            Event-driven automation on AWS
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="mt-2 h-px w-3 shrink-0 bg-accent"></span>
            Tracking down performance and stability problems
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="mt-2 h-px w-3 shrink-0 bg-accent"></span>
            Moving legacy systems forward without the downtime
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-paper-200">How I work</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2.5 text-sm text-paper-400">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="mt-2 h-px w-3 shrink-0 bg-ink-700"></span>
            Ship first, then make it better
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="mt-2 h-px w-3 shrink-0 bg-ink-700"></span>
            Own it end to end, from design to rollout
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="mt-2 h-px w-3 shrink-0 bg-ink-700"></span>
            Say the tradeoffs out loud
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="mt-2 h-px w-3 shrink-0 bg-ink-700"></span>
            Safe beats clever
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rule-top pt-6">
      <h2 class="font-mono text-[0.7rem] uppercase tracking-wide text-paper-600">
        Currently
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-paper-300">
        Working remotely at Washmen on internal platforms, analytics, and cloud
        automation. On the side I'm building MenuDash, a product of my own.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</FlowLayout>
